# Dockerized Web Application Deployment on AWS EC2

## Project Overview

This project demonstrates how to containerize a web application using Docker and deploy it on an AWS EC2 instance. 

The objective of this project is to showcase practical knowledge of:
- Docker containerization
- Image creation and management
- Cloud deployment using AWS EC2
- Linux server configuration
- Networking and port mapping

---

## Architecture Workflow

1. Created a web application
2. Wrote a Dockerfile to containerize the application
3. Built Docker image locally
4. Pushed Docker image to Docker Hub
5. Launched EC2 instance on AWS
6. Installed Docker on EC2
7. Pulled image from Docker Hub
8. Ran container with port mapping
9. Accessed application via EC2 Public IP

---

## Technologies Used

- Amazon Web Services (AWS EC2)
- Docker
- Docker Hub
- Linux
