## How to Run Locally

### Clone the Repository

git clone https://github.com/Aditya-Upadhaya/docker-aws-ec2-project.git

cd docker-aws-ec2-project


### Build Docker Image

docker build -t my-app .


### Run Container

docker run -d -p 80:3000 my-app


Open browser:
http://localhost

---

##  Deployment on AWS EC2

1. Launch EC2 instance (Amazon Linux / Ubuntu)
2. Install Docker
3. Pull image from Docker Hub

docker pull <your-dockerhub-username>/<image-name>

4. Run container

docker run -d -p 80:3000 <image-name>

5. Allow HTTP (Port 80) in Security Group
6. Access application using EC2 Public IP

